# .linkcheck-ignore — URL substrings that the link checker should skip.
#
# One substring per line. A URL is skipped if any line is `contains`-matched.
# Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
#
# Only list hosts here that are known to produce *false positives* — i.e.
# hosts that are reachable in a real browser but block non-browser clients
# at the WAF layer. Investigated on 2026-04-09; see the commit that
# introduced this file for per-host evidence.

# --- Hosts that block all programmatic checking ---
linkedin.com                 # returns HTTP 999 to all non-browser clients
www.coe.int                  # 403 to programmatic clients even with browser UA

# --- Hosts that serve 4xx to unfamiliar User-Agents ---
www.finma.ch                 # 400 to custom UAs; browser-verified reachable
nvlpubs.nist.gov             # 404 to non-browser UAs; browser-verified reachable
www.congress.gov             # 403 to non-browser UAs
media.defense.gov            # 403 to non-browser UAs
www.fiercebiotech.com        # 403 on RSS to non-browser UAs
www.ema.europa.eu            # aggressive rate limiting (429)
www.fda.gov                  # 404 to non-browser UAs (WAF); browser-verified reachable

# --- Endpoints that are not GET-addressable pages ---
formspree.io/f/              # contact form POST endpoint — 400 on GET is correct
